But the doubt will suggest itself, and finds some confirmation from the fact that the Esc. extracts give these three verses (in this order 278—276—277) after 261 (wrongly written Turpe silent artes m'les inopesque relicte) not after 277.

And this feeling of doubt will assert and re-assert itself perpetually in every fresh survey of these lections. The goodness of some, the apparent certainty of a few, amongst them, at first sway the reader to unhesitating acceptance of the whole collection.
